    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD is a superlative example of rotary engineering, preserved in showroom condition. The 13B-REW power plant retains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, delivering precise boost response with no evidence of seal degradation or housing wear. All critical vacuum lines have been overhauled to maintain pneumatic solenoid integrity, ensuring the complex sequential transition remains seamless. The chassis exhibits factory-spec rigidity, featuring the original double-wishbone suspension with forged aluminum control arms to minimize unsprung mass. Compression results are stellar and uniform across all rotor faces. With a pristine undercarriage and zero oxidative fade on the original finish, this FD offers a turnkey experience for the purist seeking peak longitudinal-engine, rear-drive dynamics.",
